.TH LSC "1" "June 2026" "lsc 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lsc \- manual page for lsc 0.1.0
.SH DESCRIPTION
lsc \- eza listing with an aligned comment column.
.PP
Allows annotating files (and directories) with short comments that show up
in a column next to file names in an `eza` listing.
.PP
Comments can come from two places, in order of precedence:
.IP
1. an inline magic line near the top of a text file:
.TP
//
#comment: <text>   (case\-insensitive, optional indent)
.IP
2. a per\-directory manifest, MANIFEST_NAME, mapping filename \-> comment.
.IP
This is plain JSON content, so it can sync through iCloud and travels with
the directory (unlike, e.g., xattrs, which iCloud sync may strip).
.PP
Manage the manifest with action flags (any other args specify the path to list):
.TP
lsc
list the current directory with comments
.TP
lsc DIR
list specified directory (one dir only; with
multiple paths or globs, comments resolve
against the current directory)
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-fetch\-icloud\fR, \fB\-\-fetch\fR
read evicted iCloud files too (forces iCloud
download if needed; default skips this)
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-no\-hilite\-recent\fR,
don't highlight just\-changed comments (on by
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-hilite\fR
default)
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-hilite\-recent\fR,
highlight just\-changed comments (if default disabled)
.HP
\fB\-\-hilite\fR
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-set\fR FILE TEXT
set FILE's manifest comment (empty TEXT removes
it, same as '\-\-rm')
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-rm\fR
FILE                remove FILE's manifest comment, if any
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-get\fR FILE
print FILE's effective comment (inline or manifest)
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-version\fR
show version number
.TP
lsc \fB\-\-help\fR
show this help
.IP
(any other flags pass thru to eza, e.g. `lsc \fB\-la\fR \fB\-\-color\fR=\fI\,never\/\fR`)
.PP
\fB\-\-set\fR and \fB\-\-rm\fR warn (on stderr) but still act when an in\-file magic line shadows
the manifest, since the magic line is still what a listing will actually show.
.PP
A manifest entry keyed "." (set with `lsc \fB\-\-set\fR . "..."`) is the directory's own
caption: it prints left\-aligned, in the comment style, as a header line above
the listing.
